The `IsSelected` Trigger in your ComboBox Style has no effect, because a ComboBox does not have such a property.

You should instead declare a Style for the ComboBoxItem class like shown below, and perhaps also add a Trigger for the `IsMouseOver` property.

    &lt;Style x:Key=&quot;ButtonBackground&quot; TargetType=&quot;ComboBoxItem&quot;&gt;
        &lt;Setter Property=&quot;Foreground&quot; Value=&quot;#047F89&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;Style.Triggers&gt;
            &lt;Trigger Property=&quot;IsSelected&quot; Value=&quot;True&quot;&gt;
                &lt;Setter Property=&quot;Foreground&quot; Value=&quot;White&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;/Trigger&gt;
            &lt;Trigger Property=&quot;IsMouseOver&quot; Value=&quot;True&quot;&gt;
                &lt;Setter Property=&quot;Foreground&quot; Value=&quot;White&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;/Trigger&gt;
        &lt;/Style.Triggers&gt;
    &lt;/Style&gt;

Then assign the Style to the `ItemContainerStyle` property of the ComboBox:

    &lt;ComboBox ... ItemContainerStyle=&quot;{StaticResource ButtonBackground}&quot;/&gt;

And use ComboBoxItem as AncestorType in the Binding in the DataTemplate:

    Fill=&quot;{Binding Foreground,
           RelativeSource={RelativeSource FindAncestor, AncestorType=ComboBoxItem}}&quot;

